â”‚ - Strategic KPI dashboarding (margin %, capacity utilization, EBITDA)      â”‚
â”‚                                                                              â”‚
â”‚ KEY BUSINESS METRICS TRACKED:                                                â”‚
â”‚ 1. Revenue & Yield                                                           â”‚
â”‚    - Total revenue ($): Daily aggregation of all sales                      â”‚
â”‚    - Yield (kg/mÂ²/year): Facility productivity benchmark                   â”‚
â”‚    - Average price ($/kg): Market-driven, crop-specific                     â”‚
â”‚    - Units sold (kg): Daily harvest volumes                                 â”‚
â”‚                                                                              â”‚
â”‚ 2. Cost Structure Analysis                                                   â”‚
â”‚    - COGS (Cost of Goods Sold): Energy + nutrients + labor                 â”‚
â”‚    - Gross margin: Revenue - COGS                                           â”‚
â”‚    - Operating expenses: Overhead, facilities, capital                       â”‚
â”‚    - EBITDA: Operating profit (before depreciation/interest)                â”‚
â”‚                                                                              â”‚
â”‚ 3. Financial Ratios & KPIs                                                   â”‚
â”‚    - Gross margin %: Target >70% (high-margin crop production)              â”‚
â”‚    - EBITDA margin %: Target >15% (operational profitability)               â”‚
â”‚    - Payback period: Years to recover capital investment                    â”‚
â”‚    - Revenue per mÂ²: Annual revenue normalized by facility size             â”‚
â”‚    - Cost per kg: Unit economics (should trend downward with scale)         â”‚
â”‚                                                                              â”‚
â”‚ 4. Forecasting & Planning                                                    â”‚
â”‚    - Monthly revenue forecast (based on growth trends)                       â”‚
â”‚    - Seasonal adjustments (market pricing variation)                         â”‚
â”‚    - Capacity planning (could we double production?)                         â”‚
â”‚    - Breakeven analysis (minimum revenue needed)                             â”‚
â”‚                                                                              â”‚
